[quote=“Aftermath, post:68, topic:229”][quote author=zarkon926 link=topic=9.msg140943#msg140943 date=1155186201]
It was the egg that came first. The earliest ancestor of a chicken would lay an egg and when it hatched, it turned out to be more and more like a chicken. This would happen over millions of years and eventually one day, the ancestor of a chicken would lay an egg that would hatch to be the chicken we know and eat today. Makes sense?
[/quote]

Clearly this - the egg that would hatch into the first being we would call a chicken came first.[/quote]

But then that specific egg was not laid by a chicken and hence isn’t the egg we’re talking about. The chicken came first.

God spawned the chicken just like runescape did, just with wayyyyyyyyy better graphics.

Okay, but seriously, it had to have been the chicken. If the egg was first there would be nothing to sit on the egg to keep it warm or protect it, if the chicken came, first, it could mate, then could lay eggs and sit on them, viola, chickens come first.

OR you could beleive that micro-organisms evolved straight into a chicken, but then a chicken would still be first. There is only one possible way for the egg to have come first, and that is for that egg be in a warm area, not have been screwed up at all, then the chick would have to find its own food, and not starve to death.
